{
  "texts": [
    "They pretrained using a contrastive pretext task where the pairwise relationship consisted of a fragment of and the entirety of a time course, which improved AUC for all three classifiers.",
    "Evaluating on OASIS-3 [128], Fedorov et al.",
    "[130,131] proposed contrastive pretraining where positive pairs consisted of paired fMRI and T1 MRI frames.",
    "The results are mixed, with fully supervised models outperforming pretrained models for T1 volumes and vice versa for fMRI volumes, for the task of AD detection.",
    "Leveraging the multiple examples per patient available in ADNI, Zhao et al. [132] suggested a pretext task that combines a basic autoencoder with mean squared error with a regularizer intended to enforce directionality in the latent space for representations of volumes from the same patient taken at two points in time."
  ]
}